{"org":"Knowsley","wards":[{"ward":"Cherryfield","seats":1,"turnout_pct":25.6,"results_url":"https://www.knowsleynews.co.uk/local-elections-2026-live-blog/","candidates":[{"n":"David Hitchmough","p":"Independent","v":628,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"128504","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128504/8072853c-e565-4fe2-9468-7d9ed7b7ee4c.png","stmt":"Dr David Hitchmough is standing in the May 2026 local elections in Cherryfield ward.\nDavid is a lifelong Kirkby resident and community activist who decided to stand this year after the discovery of a large illegal waste dump on the boundary of Cherryfield, which adds to the many pressing issues Cherryfield is facing. David chose to stand as an Independent candidate, believing this is the best way to represent his community, as it means he will be answerable only to his community, not to a Party."},{"n":"Josie Annesley","p":"Reform UK","v":605,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"128502","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128502/0d19f144-5497-41d2-95aa-088194474212.png"},{"n":"Louise Harbour","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":572,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"38395","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/38395/566034af-5b81-4d53-bf57-5f11892d787d.png"},{"n":"Ebony Higham","p":"Green Party","v":227,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"128503"}]},{"ward":"Halewood North","seats":1,"turnout_pct":33.0,"results_url":"https://www.knowsleynews.co.uk/local-elections-2026-live-blog/","candidates":[{"n":"Brian Beddows","p":"Reform UK","v":765,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128497","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128497/d02f3859-7e77-4000-b11a-0fbef3a06707.png"},{"n":"Terry Powell","p":"Labour Party","v":708,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"17918","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/17918/bdf92703-06fc-4fe8-90bf-2e70bff1462a.png"},{"n":"Kian Houltram","p":"Green Party","v":562,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128499","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128499/6e48bc55-d04b-4287-afa9-762fa0a0300c.png"},{"n":"David Hooton","p":"Independent","v":553,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"128498","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128498/8fea8a37-e8b6-43fd-8c16-965786bb238f.png","stmt":"Hi, I’m David Hooton, many people will recognise\nme from my 9 years working for Halewood Town\nCouncil, where I supported numerous local\n community groups. \nI now work as a support worker in our \ncommunity, helping vulnerable adults to live \ntheir lives as independently as possible.\nI am also an active member and coordinator \nthe Halewood Over 50s Group, support local \ndance troupes, and am actively involved in\n organising and supporting the annual Easter\n and Christmas character parades, as well as\n the last pop-up Christmas events and prepared\n and delivered Christmas dinners for residents in\nthe community who are alone at Christmas.\n\nI have put myself forward to represent the community of Halewood North as an Independent candidate.\nUntil recently, I was a committed member of the Labour Party, but I resigned my membership in 2025 after becoming increasingly disillusioned with Labour locally in Knowsley and nationally. Time and again, residents were given false promises and pledges that were never delivered and often backtracked on.\n\nAnti-social behaviour across the ward, the lack of local services, inadequate public transport, a promised Post Office that never materialised, and a Levelling Up bid that once again excluded Halewood North, have left residents feeling forgotten and ignored. Having worked in the Halewood community for many years, I have witnessed first-hand how much our area has lost under Knowsley-led Labour councillors and how much the South Ward has gained under the Independent Councillors and it is simply not good enough.\n\nThat is why I am standing as an Independent candidate for Halewood North.\nI am passionate about helping, serving, and supporting my community. If elected as your Borough Councillor, I will stand up for what the people of Halewood North deserve. I will challenge Knowsley Borough Council at every opportunity to fight for the services, investment, and respect our community needs.","bd":"1985"},{"n":"Mark Salmon","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":101,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128500"}]},{"ward":"Halewood South","seats":1,"turnout_pct":28.6,"results_url":"https://www.knowsleynews.co.uk/local-elections-2026-live-blog/","candidates":[{"n":"Joanne Harvey","p":"Independent","v":1204,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"76589","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/76589/266c3f00-8679-45cd-8853-b9bf0e3f9e6f.png","stmt":"Hi I’m Joanne Harvey, I have been the representative for Halewood South for the past 5 years, when I first won my seat after a bi-election due to the loss of my late father Cllr Allan Harvey.\nI was successfully re-elected in 2022. \nI am dedicated to serving the community, I am committed to supporting local people and strengthening our community across Halewood. \nI will always be a strong advocate for protecting and enhancing our green spaces, as these are vital in improving wellbeing, environmental sustainability, and quality of life for all residents.\nI am committed to ensuring that Halewood gets the very best opportunities, services, and investment, always working to achieve positive outcomes for individuals, families, and the wider community. My approach is rooted in listening, partnership working, and putting residents at the heart of decision-making.\nIn 2024 I was nominated to be part of the Strong Women of Knowsley Project, celebrating inspirational women who make a meaningful difference across the borough and recognising their leadership, resilience, and contribution to local life, this was a great honour to be recognised for the work I do in our community"},{"n":"Peter Bradley","p":"Labour Party","v":750,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128505","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128505/227658d0-5290-49ed-b2dc-ae1812d3dfb5.png"},{"n":"Paula Johnson","p":"Reform UK","v":617,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128506","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128506/dcf17a5a-33c6-4df5-a83a-86e0317e9494.png"}]},{"ward":"Northwood","seats":1,"turnout_pct":24.3,"results_url":"https://www.knowsleynews.co.uk/local-elections-2026-live-blog/","candidates":[{"n":"Alexander Hitchmough","p":"Reform UK","v":849,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"117804","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/117804/b408e628-4982-42d0-8e6e-06cf355c7f89.png","stmt":"Labour politicians have neglected the people of Knowsley for 52 years. Our communities have been abandoned, job opportunities have vanished, anti social behaviour tolerated, and we have a crumbling education system that offers little hope for the future. We need visible councillors that listen to your concerns, reduce council waste and spend your taxes wisely on the essential services you need.","bd":"1976"},{"n":"Marie Roughley","p":"Labour Party","v":583,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128533","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128533/12f43abf-e373-43b8-b1a6-0452e3adac25.png"},{"n":"Neill Dunne","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":409,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"179